Blast Furnace been boring lately (I mean really boring)...so I was thinkin'.....<br>
<br>
<br>
We (private citizens and the government) should do whatever it takes to set off a nuclear device inside a tornado!<br>
<br>
Now…before you say “that’s crazy Morloc!”….just think about it a little bit Exactly what would happen?….well, we NEED to know dammit.<br>
<br>
This would be an epic contest between the hand of Man and the forces of Nature. It would be Prometheus striking back at the gods!! Who would “win”? Would the nuke disrupt the 350 mph winds and dissipate the tornado?…or would the tornado’s unimaginable driving forces simply turn the newborn mushroom cloud into a vast flaming vortex!!<br>
<br>
Say that a few times……”vast flaming vortex”. How can you NOT want to see that!<br>
<br>
I don’t know exactly how to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>get</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a nuclear device into a tornado, but I suspect that there are scientists who’ve already worked this sort of thing out somewhere. If not, we <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>could</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> always just install nukes at most trailer parks and sooner or later an  unsuspecting tornado is bound to get what’s coming to it.<br>
<br>
Before I forget, I’m talking ‘bout <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>real</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> nukes here. 1+ megaton coldwar strategic warheads, not these crappy kiloton milkduds the military is sporting now. I mean, if you’re going to do this…do it right. If you don’t take it out on your first try, I doubt you’d get a second chance. I’d have to imagine, there’s nothing worse than a wounded tornado.<br>
<br>
This isn’t just some crazy stunt btw….this <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>scientific experiment</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> which would have far-reaching benefits. Assuming the test went well, I can imagine a day…in the distant and brighter future, where ALL trailer parks would have their own preemptive-strike tornado dissipation cannons. People could rest easy each night as they lay in their beds, content with the knowledge that no tornado could ever kill them again.<br>
<br>
Who can tell what else we’d learn. Perhaps this experiment would provide the breakthroughs needed to finally generate fusion power….or perhaps some a new superweapon! …..can anyone say Flame Vortex Cannon? &lt;grin&gt; who can tell!<br>
<br>
Anyways, if anyone has any ideas to add how to get this off the ground (no pun intended)….or can tell me what the vast flaming vortex might look like, please respond!…or at least write your Congressmen or whatever.<br>
<br>
<br>
